Review ONE diff (I-wire-014 mineru25 GPU serialization, iter 2 of 5). STATIC only. APPROVE iff zero P0/P1.
Do NOT call request_user_input/interactive tools, do NOT run pytest/execute/explore repo, read ONLY the inlined diff, output ONLY verdict:+p0:+p1:+p2:.
ITER-1 P1 NOW FIXED (verify closed): the GPU lock was UNCONDITIONAL, serializing even the remote vlm-http-client do_parse (server-side concurrency) -> throughput cliff. FIX: the lock is now CONDITIONAL — acquired ONLY when backend != 'vlm-http-client' (the in-process PDFium/model-singleton race); the remote backend uses contextlib.nullcontext (no serialization).
FOCUS: confirm the in-process path is still serialized (race fixed) AND the remote path is no longer serialized (P1 closed); OUTPUT-PRESERVING (timing only, no fabrication, disclosed fallback intact); no crash/None.
=== DIFF ===
diff --git a/src/tools/access_bypass.py b/src/tools/access_bypass.py
